Quote: SCHNAPPER (<i>Pagrus unicolor </i>). ... Dr. Hector says: `There are few fishes better known in the northern parts of the Colony than the schnapper. This name, by which it is known, is adopted from Australia, its Maori name, tamure, being seldom used by Europeans. It represents in these seas the braize of the European markets, ...'
